NAME
    Data::Format::Pretty::Perl - Pretty-print data structure as Perl code

VERSION
    version 0.03

SYNOPSIS
     use Data::Format::Pretty::Perl qw(format_pretty);
     print format_pretty($data);

    Some example output:

    *   format_pretty({a=>1, b=>2})

         { a => 1, b => 2 }

DESCRIPTION
    This module uses Data::Dump to format data as Perl code.

FUNCTIONS
  format_pretty($data, \%opts)
    Return formatted data structure as Perl code. Currently there are no
    known options.

  content_type()
SEE ALSO
    Data::Format::Pretty

